Lockdown around the world has brought communities together even though they are being kept apart. Video: Supplied JOHANNESBURG - Lockdown around the world has brought communities together even though they are being kept apart. From videos of police in Italy singing in the streets to uplift the spirits of their communities to the live streaming of well-known music artists around the world. READ: Slinging the lockdown lingo South Africans are never going to be left on the sidelines when it comes to performing. In the small suburb of Northwold in Johannesburg, an up-and-coming singer Kristen Anderson took it upon herself to host a street concert for her neighbours who camped out in their gardens and driveways to enjoy the show and discuss life during the lockdown and how President Cyril Ramaphosa has handled it. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.